FROM (VALUES
  ('a9637bbc-d262-516f-83a5-90dbd35a652c', 'HPS_RF_005', 'IND_HPS_D04', 'RF005_DR01', 'Quality Executive operates in Hospital Quality and Medical Records Operations within Healthcare Providers & Services, where the workplace setting involves patient access, admission, ward-status, discharge readiness and supervised handoff documentation. It handles inputs and evidence such as quality checklist; incident report; audit evidence folder; CAPA tracker; patient-safety indicator log. Day to day, the role checks quality evidence and audit checklist records, notices missing details, mismatched values, timing gaps, safety cues or unresolved handoff items, updates Quality management system; NABH audit tracker; incident reporting tool; CAPA register; document control system, prepares quality evidence and audit checklist, and escalates items requiring clinical judgement, licensed sign-off, safety decision or authority beyond the support-role boundary. The role supports routine coordination, documentation, queue/status updates, evidence preparation and supervised handoff; it does not take diagnosis, prescription, counselling, treatment, interpretation, clearance or independent clinical decision authority. Its role-environment RIASEC alignment is CIE (Conventional / Investigative / Enterprising), reflecting structured healthcare evidence control, patient/service coordination and boundary-safe escalation behaviour.', 'C', 'I', 'E', 'CIE', 'Quality Executive is mapped to CIE because Hospital Quality and Accreditation Support in Hospital Quality and Medical Records Operations uses structured records, checklist discipline, patient/service coordination, controlled system updates and escalation routing. Conventional / Investigative / Enterprising is relevant because the role combines evidence accuracy, support communication and service-specific judgement about when to stop and escalate, while producing proof such as quality evidence and audit checklist.', 'Checks patient ID, order, bed/ward, payer or MRD evidence before status update; records acknowledgement and timestamp; escalates missing order, payer mismatch, discharge blocker or safety cue.', 'Quality Executive works in Hospital Quality and Medical Records Operations within Healthcare Providers & Services. The role context is patient access, admission, ward-status, discharge readiness and supervised handoff documentation; its work is evidenced through quality checklist; incident report; audit evidence folder; CAPA tracker; patient-safety indicator log and system records such as Quality management system; NABH audit tracker; incident reporting tool; CAPA register; document control system.', 'Quality Executive: checks quality evidence and audit checklist against current case or queue requirement; reviews role inputs and exceptions in Hospital Quality and Medical Records Operations; updates Quality management system; NABH audit tracker; incident reporting tool; CAPA register; document control system; prepares quality evidence and audit checklist; escalates Escalate missing orders, consent mismatch, abnormal vitals, critical values, privacy issues, patient safety risks and emergency conditions. or any item needing clinical, licensed, safety, privacy or supervisor authority.', 'Quality Executive output evidence includes: Quality Executive checklist or record with identifiers, status, timestamp and exception notes; Quality Executive tracker update showing queue/status/handoff progress; Quality Executive escalation or handoff note naming the owner and unresolved issue; Quality Executive evidence pack with supporting documents, system screenshots/logs where applicable and reviewer acknowledgement.', '{"numerical_reasoning": 60.0, "logical_reasoning": 85.0, "verbal_reasoning": 60.0, "spatial_reasoning": 45.0, "data_interpretation": 82.0, "pattern_recognition": 83.0}'::jsonb, '{"openness": 3.0, "extraversion": 3.0, "agreeableness": 4.0, "conscientiousness": 5.0, "emotional_stability": 4.0}'::jsonb, '{"impact": 3.0, "status": 3.0, "autonomy": 2.0, "security": 5.0, "financial": 3.0, "lifestyle": 5.0, "creativity": 3.0, "leadership": 3.0}'::jsonb, '{"areas": ["Logical Reasoning", "Pattern Recognition", "Data Interpretation"], "rationale": "Quality Executive depends most on logical reasoning; pattern recognition; data interpretation because the work involves matching identifiers, checking source documents, updating systems, recognising exception cues and preparing traceable handoff evidence. Lower readiness should trigger bridge practice rather than automatic rejection unless the role is safety, licence or authority gated."}'::jsonb, '{"traits": ["Conscientiousness", "Agreeableness", "Emotional Stability"], "rationale": "Quality Executive benefits from conscientiousness; agreeableness; emotional stability because the role requires accurate evidence handling, supervised communication, privacy discipline and calm exception escalation. These traits should adjust confidence and coaching focus, not act as a hard exclusion rule."}'::jsonb, '{"values": ["Lifestyle Fit", "Security", "Creativity/Learning"], "rationale": "Quality Executive aligns best with learners who value lifestyle fit; security; creativity/learning because the environment involves structured service support, reliable documentation, patient-facing or internal coordination and visible evidence of completed work. Work values should prioritise role options, not prove technical ability."}'::jsonb, 'Preferred', 'Health Information Management; Hospital Administration; Medical Records Technology; Any degree with documentation exposure', true),
